CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "PRODIGY ACCLAIMED - Talented 13-year-old Philippa Schuyler won acclaim from all of Pittsburgh's music critics when she thrilled a capacity audience in a piano recital at Schenley High School last Thursday... Courier Photo by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Philippa Duke Schuyler wearing light colored dress and headband, and women, standing in receiving line, possibly at Schenley High School, after piano recital from Schuyler
